  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Can I deactivate my Roku device?",
  "response": "Yes, you can deactivate your Roku device. Deactivating your Roku device typically involves removing it from your Roku account, which can be useful if you're selling the device, giving it away, or simply no longer using it. Below are the steps to deactivate your Roku device:\n\n### **Method 1: Deactivate Directly from the Roku Device**\n\n1. **Turn on Your Roku Device:**\n   - Ensure your Roku device is connected to your TV and powered on.\n\n2. **Navigate to Settings:**\n   - Using your Roku remote, press the **Home** button.\n   - Scroll up or down and select **Settings**.\n\n3. **Select System:**\n   - In the Settings menu, navigate to **System**.\n\n4. **Go to Advanced System Settings:**\n   - Within the System menu, choose **Advanced system settings**.\n\n5. **Select Factory Reset:**\n   - Scroll down and select **Factory reset**.\n   - You may be prompted to enter a code displayed on the screen to confirm the reset.\n\n6. **Confirm the Reset:**\n   - Follow the on-screen instructions to complete the factory reset.\n   - This will remove all personal information and account associations from the Roku device.\n\n### **Method 2: Deactivate via the Roku Website**\n\nIf you no longer have access to the Roku device or prefer to deactivate it remotely, you can do so through the Roku website:\n\n1. **Visit the Roku Account Page:**\n   - Go to [my.roku.com](https://my.roku.com/) and sign in with your Roku account credentials.\n\n2. **Access My Account:**\n   - Once logged in, you'll see a list of your registered Roku devices.\n\n3. **Remove the Device:**\n   - Find the device you want to deactivate.\n   - Click on the **Remove** or **Deactivate** option next to the device.\n\n4. **Confirm Removal:**\n   - Follow any additional prompts to confirm that you want to remove the device from your account.\n\n### **Additional Considerations**\n\n- **Factory Reset:** Performing a factory reset not only deactivates the device but also clears all personal settings, accounts, and preferences. This is especially important if you plan to sell or give away the device.\n\n- **Account Access:** After deactivation, the Roku device will no longer have access to your Roku account, and any channels or subscriptions linked to it will be removed.\n\n- **Support:** If you encounter any issues while trying to deactivate your Roku device, consider reaching out to [Roku Support](https://support.roku.com/) for further assistance.\n\n### **Summary**\n\nDeactivating your Roku device is a straightforward process that can be done directly from the device or through your Roku account online. Whether you're preparing to pass the device on to someone else or simply want to remove it from your account, following the steps above will ensure that your Roku device is properly deactivated.\n\nIf you have any specific concerns or run into issues during the deactivation process, feel free to ask for more detailed guidance!",
